caption: Very clean on Saturday.  Good food
honestly so good. some of the best sandwiches ever. also their socially distanced setup is great and all employees were wearing their masks!!!

This place has everything I personally look for in my dining experience no matter what the setting may be. Taste: always great options for everyone, nodo pork is go to, as well as the steak sandwich or blt.  Wraps are also delcious. Quality: always seems fresh, and ALWAYS made to order.  Have some fun specials usually, as well. Consistency: ALWAYS consistently tasty and portions same.  Do wish they gave more fries per order, but probably best for my waistline they do not...
Amazing sandwiches!!!! Great service too!
Great food and lots of tasty vegetarian options.
Good service, good food.
Great sandwiches
It is the fries for me🔥
Great food.  The portion of fries I got for the whole separate order of them felt a little skimpy, but atleast they were fresh.

First time in Iowa City and was walking around.  Saw the menu and figured we would pop in for lunch. The #23 - Nido Pork sandwich did not disappoint.  Wife had the special, Roasted Butternut on gluten free bread, and really enjoyed that too.  Would 100 come back again if in town.
Efficient, friendly service and GREAT food. I've tried a few different wraps and sandwiches; my husband generally sticks to the C&P and it's always good
We stopped in to get sandwiches for lunch; their C&P is a favorite of mine. Nice staff, good food.
Great variety of flavors. Fresh and well prepared dishes. Inexpensive, especially considering the high quality. Worth checking out.
Nodo is so delicious, great vegetarian options. Also the staff are very kinds!
sandwiches are expensive for how small they are
Always good sandwiches with great flavors. Best sweet potato fries too👍🏾

This place is one of my favorite places in Iowa city. Everything on the menu is delicious. The staff is always having a good time. Would highly recommend. It’s great food at a great price and they get the food out to you very fast.
One of the best places to eat in town.
Friendly staff and outdoor seating.  Food was fresh, unique varieties of wraps and sandwiches, and good value!
Cute patio. Friendly staff. Mushroom spinach sandwich was delicious.

Really great experience! Passing through the state and stopped here for lunch. Not only were they able to answer allergen questions without sounding rushed or annoyed, but they wereawere flexible with their menu and even ran after me down the sidewalk to give me part of my order that was forgotten. I appreciate the awesome customer service and will definitely stop here the next time I'm in Iowa City.
best sandwiches in Iowa city! DO NOT SLEEP ON NODO
Love this place. Drove around for an hour to find it because I couldn't remember the name or where exactly it was.

On Tuesday, February 4th, 2020 I went in to the downtown NODO location around 1:00 pm and I ordered the number 2 which is the chorizo Breakfast burrito...while waiting nearly 30 min for my food I observed the cooks. What I saw made me nauseous. There were 3 cooks on the line, the 1st one had beard and for 90% of the time I was there he was handling food without gloves on. I saw him cough into his hands and not wash them he also would touch his face and beard and not wash his hands. The 2nd cook who I saw answer phone calls with no gloves on then go make food with no gloves on and did not wash his hands either. he put gloves on at one point and went from making food to handling the cash register and debit cards back to making food with the same gloves on  The whole time I was there I was trying to convince myself to just eat what I get, what I am seeing that it is not that bad, it will test my immune system, but the more i saw i couldn't stomach the thought of eating what I ordered. so I went up to get my money back and that is when I noticed the 3rd cook who was out of my view when I was sitting down...only god knows what he could of been doing...
Delicious food and excellent service! Try the west coast wrap, or anything else here, its all good!
Excellent gluten free menu
The French fries are to die for
Pork sandwich was BOMBBB
Killer place with a really friendly owner and cool staff!!!   Food was great
All if it! !!!

Great egg sandwich for breakfast crowd. My favorite sandwich for lunch or dinner is the mango ham sandwich. Hubby likes steak sandwich. With so many choices, you can eat there several times a week and have a variety of meals. Also great cookies.
Sandwiches are high quality
My new favorite place!

Everything on the menu tastes great but be prepared to pay $10 for a sandwich on grocery-store sized bread with no sides. Always expect to wait a while for your food, no matter how empty the place is. If you don’t mind the wait or prices, it’s definitely worth a stop.

Great local hole in the wall sandwich shop with excellent options. From inventive takes on classics to some unique offerings, it's all great. Even have some excellent vegan stuff, that meat eaters can enjoy too.
The Bacon sandwich is great. Always go for the fries and garlic aioli. Highly recommend.
Very friendly guys. Food options are amazing and very delicious. I tried their grilled cheese sandwich and it was delicious. I highly recommend this place for quick bit sandwiches and hangout.
I usually love this place but 25 min for an egg sandwich when there is 8 people on the kitchen is no bueno. Should have stood in line at Breugers, still would have been faster.
simply amazing. steak sandwich with the sauce and fries with garlic aioli.... do i need to say anymore?! go check it out for your self.
My favorite downtown Iowa City spot.
Good food.   Gluten free options too.
We really enjoy this sandwich shop.   They have many choices, even vegetarian options.  Also the sandwiches are different than you'd see elsewhere, in amazing combinations.
Super dining experience every time. They allow dogs at the outdoor seating. We love it here
The menu can be kinda overwhelming for a first visit, but everything on there is delicious! Would always recommend adding fries to your order. It's totally worth the extra 2 or 3 dollars
mushroom sandwich was soooo good. the hoisin wrap was delicious as well.
Excellent sandwiches, beverages, and BREW CITY FRIES!
Great sandwiches.  I've been eating the chorizo burrito a lot , but they have a new banh mi sandwich that was very tasty. Best French fries downtown. I prefer the sweet potato but both are excellent.

Music that played was extremely inappropriate. "N" word after "N" word. The student who was cooking the meal didnt wear gloves until after he touched the toppings for the sandwich.  Was recommended - not impressed
They have an excellent salad made with turkey and fruit.  Just be cute to enunciate the menu number you want and be very patient during a rush

The salmon melt was a huge disappointment. It looked like someone puked on my sandwich and threw a tomato on it. I was expecting an egg and a piece of salmon. What i got was a messy disaster of what looked like small pieces of egg and 'fish' ground up in some kind of sauce or batter. I could have a better salmon sandwich at Brueggers Bagels for half of the price. Most everything else is delicious at Nodo, how did they go so wrong on this??

Amazing sandwiches and great service. I always get the ham and mango. The fries are some of the best in town and come with aioli! Don't miss out on them. Just recently tried the hatch green chili Philly and it was perfect. Never a bad experience here.
Delicious, clean, fast, friendly, kind, wholesome, wonderful experience.
Great sandwiches.  I've always gone to the other location and visited this one for the first time it's a nice location with the same great sandwiches.
Newer fresh place downtown Iowa City with outdoor, inside and upstairs seating. Fresh food friendly staff and unique menu. Definitely worth the stop when looking for a new place.
Great place to get food downtown with a huge menu that never disappoints. Always get fries & aioli!
Best fries around. Delicious food, decent atmosphere.
Cute place to eat and the food was delicious
Nodo has the best sandwiches in town (and beyond) served by people who really care about you having a great experience. I travel a lot and this might be my favorite restaurant in the world.
The Homer is probably the best sandwich available in Iowa City.
Decent place for lunch, a tad pretentious.
Always delicious!  Highest quality ingredients!  I had the West Coast Wrap with grilled chicken.

Delicious for breakfast, lunch, or dinner! They have great gluten free options and the mushroom sandwich is TO DIE FOR. Get the sweet potato fries with garlic aioli, and a blueberry lemonade. The C + P is legit the best sandwich in Iowa City. And they serve daily scones (savory and sweet) for you lucky people who can eat gluten. Oh, and Coke in a bottle! Eat here.
Taste good but way to expensive. 11.95 for a chicken wrap with no sides.
They serve Sandwiches and salads but don't let that change your mind. They take classic flavors and make great dishes. Sandwiches are like 7 to 10 dollars and I thinks it's definitely worth it.
Always super tasty and a lot of unique options available as well as vegetarian choices! I recommend fries!!!

Nodo does an awesome job every time I visit.
Sandwiches are great.
great customer service
Friendly staff and great food.
Great locally inspired sandwiches in the heart of downtown Iowa City
Good tunes and friendly staff. The music is a hair loud for studying, but a nice vibe still
Ham and Mango is amazing

This place rocks!  The sandwiches are amazing and interesting.  The staff is very friendly and the upstairs is unique for a eating establishment.  There is a booth with an open window on the ceiling that let's in great light.  If you have a guest that is arriving late, you can order their sandwich and they will keep it warm for you until they arrive.  The sweet potatoe fries are superior.
Great

The sandwiches are ok, but I thought they were a little pricey, it still feels like a take out place.  The last time I went, the sandwiches were no longer warm.  I got the sweet potato fries and they were yummy, but for $3 I only got about 8 fries.  At least the menu is pretty creative and they do change up some sandwich specials every now and then.
Accidentally ordered the turkey apple salad. Glad I did because it exceeded my expectations!!
Such a big selection of sandwiches. Great atmosphere and service. All food we tried was amazing and filling. Lots of vegetarian and vegan options also.
Best sweet potato fries in Iowa City’s Downtown😍
Great food

This place is yummy! They have creative sandwiches, and a great staff. They serve brew city fries, and sweet potato fries, super good.  It's got a small store front, that's easy to ignore, but make sure to stop by sometime. They also have another location on Dodge Street.
Such a cute little cafe with excellent food, including many vegetarian options
Essential IC eating, great atmosphere, excellent food. Get the fries.
Great food!

I looooove the grilled stash sandwich and dream of the sweet potato fries with aioli. Also really like their salads and their BLT. It's cool how they display local artists artwork an upstairs is a great place to have a lunch meeting.
nodo steak with sweat potato fries. Yup.
Great prices and a nice selection. Accomodates dietary restrictions
A good place for sandwiches. A few options for vegetarians as well.
great sandwiches and fries!  steak sandwich with brew city fries with aioli are excellent. pork sandwich, breakfast, salmon all are excellent. great music selection and fairly priced beers too.
The salmon sandwich was excellent
Could live off their egg sandwich alone.
Food is fresh and a verity to satisfy many types of tastes! I personally like the veriety of fresh vegetables and meat and home made breads for there sandwiches. Also home made soups! 😆
Love the fresh and creative menu. Great food, higher prices but worth it. Dining area is a bit chaotic, but I'll be back.
Delicious food and shakes are awesome but price is high!

I've been going to Iowa for a few years now, and this is by far my favorite place to eat. The staff is really laidback and friendly, the entire place has a mellow vibe, and they provide great vegetarian, gluten free, and vegan options (awesome for friends with dietary restrictions).  By far, my favorite is the Ham & Mango Sandwich - to die for!
Pretty great except for the chicken artichoke sandwich and burgers.  fries are really good.
Love the food
The cashier is a hipster douche bag with a nose ring. Someone should of given her a hug as a child. Food is good.
Bad burger, but great sweet potato fries.
The food is excellent. I had a ham, cheese, and mango sandwich with sweet potato fries. Would recommend it to anyone!
Unique menu, quick service, tasty food.
Love the sandwiches here
Love this place, it feels like there is a sandwich for everyone on this menu. I found the Bacon as mine. Also try to brew city fries.
You have to visit for lunch or dinner! The #4 steak sandwich is the best! Love the fries and their breakfast sandwiches!

Best place to eat lunch in town. You truly can not go wrong with any of their sandwiches. The fries both reg and sweet are delicious. They also bake a mean scone and cookies. My personal favorites are the nodo steak and the C&P. The whole menu is worth trying though. A definite must for eating in Iowa City.

I'm a picky eater so when my friend suggested we go here I was apprehensive. I ordered some bacon sandwich and it was delicious! I will admit that this place is expensive. For a sandwich, drink and a side you could spend $10-15 depending on what you order. I would not go here very often however, I would treat myself to this every now and then.
Out of the two times I've been to Nodo. I have had great service and excellent food. The dishes are very unique.
Food is great, but I've stopped going there because they're always playing loud, vulgar music. Either guttural death metal or obscene rap. Really don't like being shouted at when I'm eating.
Love that they have gluten-free bread options available
Great sandwiches and salads!
Best fries around
good moderately priced food, friendly staff, great sweet potato fries
Super delicious sandwiches and fries.

This one of the highest rated restaurants in Iowa city, and for good reason. They have amazing sandwiches and fries. Seriously, one of the best sandwiches I've had. I really love the portabello sandwich-- delish!
Creative, tasty & inexpensive sandwiches in a no-frills environment. While there isn't table service, the staff seems committed to accommodating and serving everyone.
Excellent place. We stop here every time we visit Iowa City and it never ceases to exceed our expectations. Nodo demonstrates that a little diversity and creativity in a menu will not hurt anyone.
Great sandwiches and wraps. High quality but quick enough to grab a bite between classes.
The natural and organic food menu items are just so delicious and get made fresh in front of you!! Great beer selection and great music!
Easily the best sandwiches in town, and less expensive than the other dedicated sandwich places. The mushroom sandwich is phenomenal. Upstairs seating is spacious and usually quieter.

Great experience. Fries were fresh, and I took a risk with the $10 steak sandwich, but I'm glad I did because it was really tasty.  Will be back. Love that they have a more private upstairs seating area. They even bused our table for us after we left. Felt bad that I didn't leave a tip.

Great service and awesome food! It is a great Iowa City spot
Best sandwich shop in town. Try the ham and mango.
Tasty food choices.
Cozy little sandwiches shop with in walking distance of a lot of entertaining sites.
So many tasty options! The cobb wrap or the bacon!! Yum 😋
I just experience a very rude cashier there will never go back!

Problem: you're hungry. Solution: Nodo Downtown. Seriously, THE BEST SANDWICHES I've had on either side of the Mississippi. We came here a lot while were in town, especially for breakfast. Prices are higher than you'd like to see, but all in all, well-priced. Good service.

Nodo offers a sandwich menu with a ton of variety and creativity.  I got the ham & mango and it was fantastic.  The fries were hands down the best fries in town and the soup was pretty good too.  Iowa City restaurants need to take a note from Nodo and put more effort into maintaining a reverence for great food and not just pandering to hungry college students.
Very good food, prices a little bit expensive

This is one of the best sandwich shops in Iowa City! Great flavor combinations, fast service (even during the lunch rush!), and some of the best fries I've ever had. I highly recommend the #1 (egg sandwich), #7 (ham & mango), #12 (turkey & cranberry wrap), and #23 (Nodo pork).
Amazingly creative food
This place is amazing. Everything on the menu is absolutely delicious. They'll even let you make your own sandwich so they can cater to all tastes.
Very good I had the #8 c&p and two hearted ipa👌🏽
Creative and delicious sandwiches and salads.  Fries are absolutely the best in town and the service is fantastic!  Love this place!
Some of most innovative and tasty sandwiches in River City
The C & P was amarzing. Will definitely be back
